SIMPLE: fortuitous
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fortuitous
<hw>For*tu"i*tous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>fortuitus</ets>; akin to <ets>forte</ets>, adv., by chance, prop.
abl. of <ets>fors</ets>, <ets>fortis</ets>, chance. See
<er>Fortune</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Happening by chance; coming or
occuring unexpectedly, or without any known cause; chance; <as>as, the
<ex>fortuitous</ex> concourse of atoms</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It was from causes seemingly <qex>fortuitous</qex> . . . that all
the mighty effects of the Reformation flowed.</q>
<rj><qau>Robertson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>So as to throw a glancing and <qex>fortuitous</qex> light upon the
whole.</q> <rj><qau>Hazlitt.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(LAw)</fld> <def>Happening independently of human
will or means of foresight; resulting from unavoidable physical
causes.</def> <rj><au>Abbott.</au></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Accidental; casual; contingent; incidental. See
<er>Accidental</er>.</syn></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>For*tu"i*tous*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>For*tu"i*tous*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fortuity</ent>⟦br⟧
